property.name: text
property.value:
This model launches a web server and provides a service available at http://localhost:8074/guidance?rate=0
This service was designed to showcase Sensor Andrew's mobile phone indoor localization capabilities.
A map shows the location of five markers, numbered 1 through 5, which correspond to up to five mobile devices. Each mobile device periodically POSTs its location (X, Y coords) and ID number to http://localhost:8074/guidance
A GET request to the above URL will show the map and all markers. The map will refresh at the given rate (enter 0 if refresh is not desired). The rate paramter is required.
Please run the model and navigate to the above URL (or run the model and double click on this comment). (For some reason this model is slow to open a browser window...)

property.name: text
property.value: HTMLModelExporter creates a web page from the specified model. Make sure directoryToExportTo is set to $TMPDIR so that the WebServer can find the image generated from the model, while searching its temporaryFileLocation which is also set to $TMPDIR

property.name: text
property.value: The MicrostepDelays ensure that the web page response occurs after the request, in logical time

property.name: text
property.value: Updates the location of the marker for the given ID and returns the whole map Expects three parameters: ID (will stay a string), xCoord (converted to a double), and yCoord (converted to a double) For example: POST /guidance?ID=12&xCoord=200&yCoord=300

property.name: text
property.value: ID numbers of the mobile devices Currently hard-coded; no discovery

property.name: text
property.value: Returns the current map, which will refresh itself if rate > 0 Expects one parameter: rate (converted to an integer, in milliseconds) For example: GET /guidance?rate=30000 The page will refresh itself every 30 seconds (30000 milliseconds)

property.name: text
property.value: Set refresh rate to 0, so map will not auto-refresh

property.name: text
